1
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:58,360
<i>What happened?</i>

2
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:01,600
<i>Why am I here?</i>

3
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,920
Is anyone there?

4
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,320
You should be in your room.

5
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,720
- Not out wandering around like this.
- Why?

6
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,440
Why are you doing this to me?

7
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:07,840
Doing what?

8
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,880
I haven't done anything.

9
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,320
This isn't me.

10
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:15,480
I'm not her.

11
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,520
Why wouldn't you be?

12
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:29,720
From now on,

13
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:36,040
you are her.

14
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:11,800
SIX MONTHS EARLIER

15
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:15,280
<i>Ms. Khaedarun Kanchathara,</i>
<i>executive of TGL Group,</i>

16
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:20,680
<i>has donated 120 million baht</i>
<i>to a medical foundation</i>

17
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:23,800
<i>to purchase equipment</i>
<i>to help disaster victims.</i>

18
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:26,400
<i>Wow, that's truly admirable.</i>

19
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,400
<i>We've obtained this footage.</i>

20
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:31,160
<i>A woman helps an elderly man</i>
<i>after his handcart was hit</i>

21
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,960
<i>- by a pickup truck and tipped over.</i>
<i>- How are you, sir?</i>

22
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:36,200
<i>She takes him to the hospital.</i>

23
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:38,240
<i>We later found out</i>

24
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:44,000
<i>that woman was Ms. Khaedarun Kanchathara,</i>
<i>also known as Socialite Claire.</i>

25
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:46,800
<i>Not only is she generous,</i>
<i>she's truly admirable.</i>

26
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,080
<i>Yes.</i>

27
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,720
Ms. Claire is here.

28
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,800
<i>And finally,</i>

29
00:05:55,880 --> 00:06:00,000
<i>the Socially Responsible</i>
<i>Businesswoman of the Year Award</i>

30
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:02,280
<i>goes to…</i>

31
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:04,200
Hello, Ms. Claire.

32
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,720
<i>Ms. Khaedarun Kanchathara.</i>

33
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,240
What's today's event again?

34
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:14,880
It's an event for World Environment Day.

35
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,760
Then why did you prepare this outfit?

36
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:21,880
Well, you said today the minister
and the chairman would be there,

37
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:24,880
so we prepared
something a bit more formal.

38
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:29,920
But you were the one who chose this outfit
when the boutique sent their clothes over.

39
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,600
My job is to choose.

40
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,760
Your job…

41
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,040
is to make me stand out.

42
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:44,160
Do you think this outfit does that?

43
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,480
I'm sorry.

44
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,000
Ms. Claire.

45
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:03,040
How about something simple and elegant?

46
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:06,280
We can add
accessories to make it stand out.

47
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:10,520
I want this one.

48
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:14,640
Uh, but today's event theme is white.

49
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:18,720
Yes.

50
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,400
Start my makeup.

51
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,680
THIWA KANCHATHARA CHAIRMAN OF TGL GROUP

52
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:06,400
KHAEDARUN KANCHATHARA CEO OF TGL GROUP

53
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,360
LET'S SAVE THE EARTH WHICH IS OUR HOPE

54
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,120
Excuse me.

55
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,880
Where will you put these flowers?

56
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,360
Inside, sir.

57
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,800
Is there a problem, sir?

58
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:35,120
Hello, my name is Nitchan.

59
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:38,280
I'm TGL's Head of Strategy,
and I look after Mr. Thiwa.

60
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,919
I'd like to go in and make sure
everything is in order.

61
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:48,920
Noted. I'm the minister's security officer
overseeing this event.

62
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,720
I see. Then that's perfect.

63
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:53,240
I think the hotel may have missed my note

64
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:55,840
specifying that no flowers
are allowed at this event.

65
00:08:55,920 --> 00:09:00,600
In that case, please ask the hotel
to remove all the flowers from the event.

66
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:04,120
I'm sorry, but the event
starts in less than an hour.

67
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,160
There's no time.

68
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,600
I think the flowers look nice.

69
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:12,520
The reason for removing all the flowers
has nothing to do with how they look.

70
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:16,920
It's because
Mr. Thiwa is allergic to pollen.

71
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,960
But the event's about to start.

72
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:23,880
The minister won't be pleased
if he finds out the event isn't ready.

73
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,640
I understand.

74
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:29,760
But Mr. Thiwa is
the minister's important guest.

75
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:33,200
And if something happens to him
at this event,

76
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,440
I don't think the minister
will be pleased either.

77
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:38,600
And someone has to take responsibility.

78
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,600
Can you handle that?

79
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:48,280
The flowers can be removed in time.

80
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:50,040
There's still time.

81
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,840
Get the hotel's venue staff here.

82
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:03,840
Yes, sir.

83
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:05,800
Thank you.

84
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,480
Mr. Chan!

85
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,520
<i>- I'm sorry.</i>
<i>- How many times have I told you?</i>

86
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:16,000
<i>How is this acceptable?</i>
<i>How can I hold a meeting?</i>

87
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,400
<i>Please don't fire me.</i>

88
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:21,520
<i>- Ow!</i>
<i>- Is this all you can do?</i>

89
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:24,120
<i>If this is all you can do, then get lost!</i>

90
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,320
<i>Go!</i>

91
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:28,280
<i>Are we doing this meeting or not?!</i>

92
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:51,800
CHAN

93
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,280
What is it, Chan?

94
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:05,680
Has Ms. Claire left?
She isn't answering my calls.

95
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:09,840
<i>The styling team just called</i>
<i>to say she's getting dressed right now.</i>

96
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:13,400
Then go tell her not to come.

97
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:16,280
<i>- I'll call her and explain everything.</i>
- What happened, Chan?

98
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:20,120
Someone leaked a video of Claire
assaulting an employee.

99
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,240
But Ms. Claire has been
really looking forward to this event.

100
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,840
And the chairman wants to promote her.

101
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,800
Is this really a good idea?

102
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:31,360
Her presence will do more harm than good.

103
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:34,360
<i>We don't have much time. Go stop her.</i>

104
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:43,800
- Ms. Claire!
- Don't you know how to do makeup?

105
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:45,200
Hold still.

106
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,840
Come here.

107
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:49,680
Hold still. I'll show you how to do it.

108
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:52,280
- Ms. Claire!
- I said hold still.

109
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:55,040
Ms. Claire. I'm sorry.

110
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,720
- What's going on?
- Please don't hurt me.

111
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:58,040
Ms. Claire!

112
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,680
Hold still.

113
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:01,040
I said hold still.

114
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,240
Ms. Claire!

115
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,360
- Hold still.
- Ms. Claire.

116
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,680
- I said hold still.
- I'm sorry.

117
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:07,400
- What's going on?
- Ms. Claire, I'm sorry.

118
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:08,400
Please don't hurt me.

119
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,320
- Do you even know how?
- Leave us.

120
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:13,040
I have something important
to discuss with Ms. Claire.

121
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,560
I just don't get it.

122
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:22,120
What's so hard about
a no-makeup makeup look?

123
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:30,680
Maybe the hard part is making you
the most beautiful woman at the event.

124
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:35,960
So are you my bodyguard or theirs?

125
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,040
Did Chan send for me?

126
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:42,520
Tell him I'll make it in time.

127
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:47,320
He asked me to relay an important message.

128
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:50,720
What does he want?

129
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,760
- <i>Ow!</i>
- <i>Is this all you can do?</i>

130
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:58,080
<i>If this is all you can do, then get lost!</i>

131
00:12:58,920 --> 00:12:59,920
<i>Go!</i>

132
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,760
<i>What are you looking at?</i>

133
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,240
<i>- Get back to work.</i>
- Why?

134
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:05,360
<i>- Are we doing this meeting or not?!</i>
- The image quality is pretty good.

135
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,400
Does Chan not like it?

136
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:12,320
You're not shocked at all?

137
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:15,760
Shocked?

138
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,640
Am I supposed to be?

139
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:23,080
What crazy bitch
leaked a video to ruin me?!

140
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,520
Should I be nervous?

141
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:34,400
I don't think so. I don't want
to follow someone else's game plan.

142
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,600
Please don't go, Ms. Claire.

143
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:44,960
The reporters are waiting
at the event to report on you.

144
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,760
Please, I'm begging you.

145
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,320
Why should I be scared of them?

146
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:09,160
I'm not telling you to be scared.

147
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,360
I'm worried if you go to the event,

148
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:14,080
the chairman will be upset.

149
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:15,880
Good.

150
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:17,880
I don't want to go anyway.

151
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,600
<i>What did she say?</i>

152
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,720
I did what you asked.

153
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:39,760
I told her if she insisted on going,
the news might upset the chairman.

154
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,520
<i>So she agreed.</i>

155
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:44,160
Of course.

156
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:47,480
Everyone knows she loves
the chairman more than anything.

157
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:49,320
<i>Do you want my help there?</i>

158
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:51,600
No.

159
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:54,920
But help me contain the news
about Claire as much as you can

160
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,560
before it gets any worse.

161
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:16,560
How's it going?

162
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:18,880
Has the hotel removed all the flowers?

163
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,280
They're working on it.

164
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:24,880
And have you arranged for
the chairman's car to park in the back?

165
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,600
Yes, but…

166
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:45,280
Is everything okay, Chan?

167
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,840
Hello, Mr. Chairman.

168
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,720
Everything's fine.

169
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,200
Fine?

170
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:54,000
Then why do you have him
entering through the back?

171
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:57,240
You know it isn't appropriate
for the chairman of TGL

172
00:15:57,320 --> 00:16:00,080
to enter an event from the back.

173
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:04,080
It's just…

174
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:06,600
there are many reporters out front.

175
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:09,440
I was worried it would be inconvenient,
so I avoided them.

176
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,560
Really?

177
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:13,200
Not for some other reason?

178
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,440
That's enough.

179
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:21,520
If Chan decided,
it means he's thought it through.

180
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,640
Yes.

181
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,560
Is Claire here yet?

182
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:32,880
What is it, Chan?

183
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:38,760
Well…

184
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:42,640
I was informed she isn't feeling well.

185
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:46,280
Can she not be a problem for once?

186
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:52,320
Hey, doesn't she know

187
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:56,320
the chairman came to this event
to promote the project she's overseeing?

188
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:57,440
Rossarin.

189
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:00,960
I'm sorry.

190
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:06,280
I just want her to appreciate
your good intentions.

191
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:12,119
And what if she really is unwell?

192
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,520
Then what?

193
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:17,200
Then nothing.
I'm giving the speech today either way.

194
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:22,560
Then I'll escort you to the lounge, sir.

195
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:24,359
- Let's go.
- This way, please.

196
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,840
Hello, ma'am.

197
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:50,000
Is there anything that
has caught your eye today?

198
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:52,640
Or if you have something in mind,
please let me know.

199
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,440
How thick is this bathtub?

200
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:10,440
This bathtub is a new import.

201
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:13,480
You have excellent taste, ma'am.

202
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:14,960
I asked how thick it is.

203
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:21,880
May I ask what kind of thickness
you're looking for?

204
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:23,560
You can let me know.

205
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:31,160
I want one as thick as your face?
Do you have it?

206
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:35,600
Wh… What?

207
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:39,400
I'm dating Chris,

208
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,960
the architect you offered
to sleep with yesterday.

209
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:50,160
Ow! Ma'am, what are you doing? Wait!

210
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:51,680
Ma'am, wait!

211
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:53,760
What am I doing?

212
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:55,560
What about what you did?

213
00:18:56,120 --> 00:18:58,360
What about what you did? How could you?!

214
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,880
Please stop.

215
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,360
Stay out of it!

216
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,160
Ma'am, please don't do this.

217
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:14,280
Next time, offer him whatever you want,
but don't offer yourself.

218
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:15,320
Got it?!

219
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:21,320
And if you want to sue me…

220
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:30,600
Are you okay?

221
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,720
How is it, Mom?

222
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,680
Are you enjoying the event?

223
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:37,280
Did anyone ask anything?

224
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:41,480
What do you mean by that?

225
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:44,080
Did you know Claire wasn't coming?

226
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:47,560
Well, you were the one who said

227
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:51,240
we couldn't let her
get the TGL chairmanship.

228
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:53,280
Anyone can see that

229
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:57,960
Dad organized this event to launch the
Agriv project that Claire is overseeing.

230
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:01,560
<i>So we can't possibly</i>
<i>let this event happen.</i>

231
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:04,200
And what did you do
to make her not show up?

232
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:06,200
<i>I didn't do anything.</i>

233
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,960
She did this to herself.

234
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:10,520
I just wanted everyone to know

235
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:13,200
she isn't really the angel
everyone thinks she is.

236
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:14,680
<i>Bye.</i>

237
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,880
Your hot tea, Mr. Chairman.

238
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:22,600
Thanks a lot.

239
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:26,120
Hey, when no one else is around,
you can call me Grandpa.

240
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:31,560
It's good that he calls you Mr. Chairman.

241
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:32,800
Mm?

242
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:37,000
Otherwise, if someone hears it,
they might wonder

243
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:39,680
why your driver's son calls you Grandpa.

244
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,200
Where have you been?

245
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:49,680
I was just checking that
everything at the event was in order.

246
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:51,720
And then I found out…

247
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:54,320
why Claire didn't come.

248
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:59,640
Chan, you should
tell the chairman the truth

249
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:04,360
about why his beloved granddaughter
can't attend the event.

250
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:11,080
Where is Claire?

251
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:21,920
A video of Ms. Claire
assaulting an employee was leaked.

252
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,760
So I didn't want her to attend

253
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:29,120
because I thought the reporters
would use it against her, sir.

254
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,280
Next time something like this happens,

255
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:33,240
you should tell me and the chairman.

256
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:37,280
Otherwise, if reporters ask us
about the next TGL chairperson,

257
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:38,800
what are we supposed to say?

258
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:46,040
Do you want Cha to come instead?

259
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:50,400
Because the project
you're here to promote today

260
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:54,760
was actually Cha's idea
before it was handed over to Claire.

261
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:59,960
If Cha came,
she could be a big help to you.

262
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:01,080
No need.

263
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:06,280
I don't want people to be confused about
who is actually in charge of this project.

264
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:12,760
So where is Claire?

265
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,240
She's at home.

266
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:16,840
I have Tun keeping an eye on her.

267
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:29,800
What?

268
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:35,760
What is it, Chan?

269
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:42,400
The office called to say
there's a small issue with some documents.

270
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:44,640
Please excuse me for a moment.

271
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:48,600
Come again?

272
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:50,640
Claire's missing?

273
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:51,960
Have you really looked?

274
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:55,840
I've had people check everywhere.
She's nowhere to be found.

275
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,560
She must have snuck out the back.

276
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:00,760
- Do you think she went to the event?
- <i>No.</i>

277
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:04,000
Claire may be hot-tempered,
but she's not stupid.

278
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,600
She knows coming here
means facing reporters

279
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:08,880
and it could hurt her chances
of getting the chairmanship.

280
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:11,040
So where do you think she is?

281
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:30,600
What's up, dear?

282
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:36,280
I just called to thank you
for leaking that video.

283
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:40,240
My goodness. How did you know it was me?

284
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,080
<i>Come on now.</i>

285
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:45,520
<i>Denying what you've done</i>
<i>isn't like you at all.</i>

286
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:46,840
<i>How did I know it was you?</i>

287
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:50,160
How stupid would I have to be
not to figure it out?

288
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:53,040
<i>Oh, but it's totally fine if you deny it.</i>

289
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:58,680
So are you calling to thank me
or to interrogate me?

290
00:23:58,760 --> 00:23:59,960
Wow.

291
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:02,080
Of course, I'm calling to thank you.

292
00:24:02,160 --> 00:24:05,200
Because honestly,
I don't really want to attend that event.

293
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:07,720
Whether I attend or not,

294
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:10,680
Grandpa is gonna give me
the TGL chairmanship anyway.

295
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:13,640
<i>I'd rather spend my time</i>
<i>finding good food.</i>

296
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:17,960
Hey, do you know where I am
looking for good food right now?

297
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:20,720
I don't care
where you eat or where you die.

298
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:22,440
I don't want to know.

299
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:53,320
Ms. Claire?

300
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:56,720
What's that look on your face?
Are you happy or shocked?

301
00:24:56,800 --> 00:25:00,040
Uh, aren't you supposed to be
with the chairman?

302
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,440
Then I'll leave.

303
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:04,280
Wait, Ms. Claire.

304
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:08,080
You came all the way here.
What's the rush?

305
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,560
Is something wrong?

306
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:43,960
Ms. Claire.

307
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:45,080
Stay still.

308
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:49,800
What's wrong?

309
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,680
I want a drink.

310
00:26:53,760 --> 00:26:54,720
Go buy me some wine.

311
00:26:58,560 --> 00:26:59,520
Right now?

312
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:02,640
Yes.

313
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:05,280
I'm frustrated. I want to relax.

314
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,240
Can't you do it?

315
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:10,680
Yes, I can.

316
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:17,760
I'll be right back.

317
00:27:17,840 --> 00:27:20,360
- Don't take too long.
- I won't.

318
00:27:33,920 --> 00:27:35,600
SWIPE UP TO UNLOCK

319
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:38,400
What the hell is wrong with her?

320
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:51,400
<i>Guess where I am right now.</i>

321
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:28,920
I was just thinking about you, Cha.

322
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,400
That's perfect.

323
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:32,160
I'll stop by.

324
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,800
Uh, you can't, Cha.

325
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:35,560
<i>Why not?</i>

326
00:28:36,160 --> 00:28:37,960
Why can't I stop by?

327
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:42,240
Well, I'm about to leave to see a client.

328
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:45,360
But you told me you were free today.

329
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:48,680
Well, the client suddenly called me.

330
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:51,080
<i>I don't know how long it'll take.</i>

331
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:52,760
<i>How about we meet tomorrow?</i>

332
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:56,120
I'll make it up to you properly, Cha.

333
00:28:57,560 --> 00:29:01,160
Fine. Go get ready for your presentation.

334
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:02,400
I'll let you work.

335
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:35,560
Cha?

336
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:36,800
You bitch.

337
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:41,440
Ow, ow, Cha! Wait.

338
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,400
You!

339
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,160
Claire!

340
00:29:46,800 --> 00:29:47,640
You bitch!

341
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:50,320
How could you do this? Huh? How could you?

342
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:51,680
I haven't done anything.

343
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:52,640
No?

344
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:54,200
You say you haven't done anything?

345
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:59,760
Cha! Cha, hear me out. Cha.

346
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:02,240
Liar! Don't lie to me!

347
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:04,000
How could you do this?!

348
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:05,760
How could you do this?!

349
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:06,760
You!

350
00:30:06,840 --> 00:30:09,560
Help! Cha, hear me out!

351
00:30:09,640 --> 00:30:11,480
- Cha!
- I'm not listening!

352
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:12,640
Help!

353
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:19,320
The event has now begun,
but Ms. Khaedarun has yet to arrive.

354
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:22,520
This may be related to the video of
her assaulting an employee

355
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:24,360
that leaked earlier.

356
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:35,520
Mr. Chairman.

357
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:38,520
Reporters are waiting out front
to report on Claire.

358
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:40,040
Should we use another entrance?

359
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:42,280
- Let's go.
- Why should he run

360
00:30:42,360 --> 00:30:43,720
from something so trivial?

361
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:51,120
Yes, it's very clear.

362
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:54,560
- They're fighting.
- Why are they so violent?

363
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:59,640
He will enter through the front
with the dignity of TGL's chairman.

364
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:03,800
- That's Mr. Thiwa.
- Mr. Thiwa!

365
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:05,240
There he is!

366
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:09,520
Sir, have you heard about
the leaked video of Ms. Claire?

367
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:11,360
How will you handle this?

368
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:13,720
Excuse me. The chairman is aware of it.

369
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:17,160
But right now, please let him
focus on going onstage.

370
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:18,560
Hold your questions for now.

371
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:19,480
- This way, sir.
- Wait.

372
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:22,480
Will the physical fight between
Ms. Khaedarun and Ms. Alicha

373
00:31:22,560 --> 00:31:25,360
affect the selection of TGL chairmanship?

374
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,800
Hold on, who did you say was fighting?

375
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:32,560
Here, sir. Ms. Alicha
and Ms. Claire are fighting.

376
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:33,760
<i>Hear me out!</i>

377
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:35,760
How could something like this happen?

378
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:36,680
- What is going on?
- <i>Cha!</i>

379
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:37,760
<i>You lying bitch!</i>

380
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:38,920
What is this?

381
00:31:39,640 --> 00:31:41,000
How could this happen?

382
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:43,120
- So it's true, sir?
- Is it true, sir?

383
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:45,000
Is it true, sir?

384
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:47,480
- How will you handle this?
- Is it true, sir?

385
00:31:47,560 --> 00:31:49,480
- Sir, please say something.
- How will you handle this?

386
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:51,200
How will you handle this?

387
00:31:51,280 --> 00:31:52,120
Sir?

388
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,720
Call an ambulance now.

389
00:32:10,800 --> 00:32:12,160
- Sir?
- No photos, please.

390
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:13,360
- Mr. Thiwa!
- No photos.

391
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:15,840
No photos, please. I'm begging you.

392
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:17,680
What happened to him?

393
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:20,560
- Did anyone call for help?
- Grandpa?

394
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:23,800
- Call an ambulance.
- No photos, please.

395
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:36,760
Cha? I'm screwed.

396
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:39,760
Help!

397
00:32:39,840 --> 00:32:40,760
Cha.

398
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:42,360
Cha, stop. Cha!

399
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:43,800
- Let go.
- Cha.

400
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:44,920
Let go!

401
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,920
- Let me go!
- Stop, Cha!

402
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:47,960
Let go!

403
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:50,240
Calm down?

404
00:32:50,320 --> 00:32:52,800
You want me to calm down?
How could you do this?!

405
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:54,520
<i>- Cha, calm down.</i>
<i>- How could you?</i>

406
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:55,640
<i>- Cha.</i>
<i>- Let go!</i>

407
00:32:55,720 --> 00:32:57,520
- Cha. Cha.
- Let go!

408
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,040
- Cha.
- I hate you!

409
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:00,640
Calm down, Cha.

410
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:01,840
- Let go!
- Cha.

411
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:04,080
Oh, it hurts so much.

412
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:09,120
Now everyone knows
who the violent one actually is.

413
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:10,560
Claire.

414
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:12,880
You!

415
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:16,520
You!

416
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:20,360
Did you really think I let you hit me

417
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:23,040
because I was afraid of you? Huh?

418
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:26,280
You crazy bitch! Let me go!

419
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,240
Let go!

420
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:31,080
Do you see now that you can never beat me?

421
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:34,160
You bitch!

422
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:35,760
- Let me go!
- Cha.

423
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:37,760
- Let go!
- Enough, Cha.

424
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:39,640
- Let go!
- Cha.

425
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,800
Claire!

426
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:43,280
- You psycho!
- Cha.

427
00:33:43,360 --> 00:33:44,880
You psycho!

428
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:46,000
Let go!

429
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:47,760
Let go!

430
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:49,240
Let go!

431
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:50,920
- Let go!
- Cha!

432
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,480
Claire!

433
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:55,200
Let go!

434
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:56,920
NITCHAN

435
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:58,280
SLIDE TO ANSWER

436
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:02,520
Don't tell me
you were watching the livestream.

437
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:06,800
What?

438
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:08,440
Grandpa?

439
00:34:10,159 --> 00:34:12,159
What did you say happened to Grandpa?

440
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:24,280
For this model,

441
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:26,360
I can only give you 5,000.

442
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:27,600
Just 5,000?

443
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:31,719
Doesn't this model usually sell
for over 10,000?

444
00:34:32,600 --> 00:34:33,880
It used to.

445
00:34:33,960 --> 00:34:36,480
But this model isn't popular anymore.

446
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:38,400
To tell you the truth,

447
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:40,239
I'm giving you a wholesale price.

448
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:43,520
Some buyers would only
offer you a little over 3,000.

449
00:34:44,239 --> 00:34:46,320
So are you selling it or not?

450
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:49,040
If you are, I'll pay you right here.

451
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:54,320
Okay.

452
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,239
Five thousand.

453
00:34:56,080 --> 00:34:58,560
- I'll give you my account number.
- Hey, Jin!

454
00:34:58,640 --> 00:34:59,680
What?

455
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:01,440
Wan, what are you doing?

456
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:03,440
I should be asking you that.

457
00:35:04,320 --> 00:35:05,280
Hold on.

458
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:07,240
What's going on here?

459
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:09,440
She stole my camera.

460
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:11,640
- Stole?
- Yes.

461
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:15,400
Or did you place an order
and have her steal my camera?

462
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:17,920
Hey, I don't know anything.
This has nothing to do with me.

463
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,400
I'm not buying it anymore.
It's stolen goods.

464
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:22,200
Hey, wait.

465
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:23,200
- I didn't steal it!
- Jin.

466
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,160
What the hell, Wan?

467
00:35:25,240 --> 00:35:27,480
You know how desperate I am
to have to do this.

468
00:35:27,560 --> 00:35:29,360
Hey, can you just hear me out?

469
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:31,280
I know you're angry,

470
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:34,160
but I'm doing this to help you.

471
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:37,640
Help me?

472
00:35:38,160 --> 00:35:42,400
He might have been the first
and last person to want to buy my camera.

473
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:45,840
Move.

474
00:35:46,720 --> 00:35:49,440
But your aunt bought you this camera
when you were in school.

475
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:53,680
And you love it.
That's why I don't want you to sell it.

476
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:57,080
If I don't sell it,

477
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:02,320
where am I supposed to get money
to buy her medicine?

478
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:04,080
I haven't gotten my salary.

479
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:07,000
Hey.

480
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:08,800
See?

481
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:13,920
You were so busy trying to sell it
that you didn't check my messages.

482
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,560
I already transferred you 10,000.

483
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:29,400
TRANSFER COMPLETE 10,000 BAHT

484
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,000
Wan.

485
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:35,880
Are you crazy?

486
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:39,320
It's too much.
How will you last the whole month?

487
00:36:39,400 --> 00:36:42,960
Oh, I'll have plenty.
I don't have any expenses anyway.

488
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:46,840
And I know Alzheimer's medication
is expensive.

489
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:50,120
You need it way more than I do.
Just take it.

490
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:53,280
Wan…

491
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,120
Wan.

492
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:00,160
Wan.

493
00:37:00,240 --> 00:37:01,560
Thank you so much.

494
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:05,640
If I don't help my best friend,
who else am I supposed to help?

495
00:37:37,120 --> 00:37:38,480
What happened to Grandpa?

496
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:41,520
He is safe now.

497
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:44,080
Wait.

498
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:47,680
I don't think you should go in yet.

499
00:37:47,760 --> 00:37:48,960
Why not?

500
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:52,120
Hello, Ms. Claire.

501
00:37:53,320 --> 00:37:55,200
Mr. Thiwa is safe now.

502
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:57,160
We've given him a thrombolytic.

503
00:37:58,320 --> 00:37:59,400
What happened to him?

504
00:38:02,120 --> 00:38:03,920
Why did he need a thrombolytic?

505
00:38:05,520 --> 00:38:08,160
Mr. Thiwa had
an acute myocardial infarction.

506
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:13,920
Thank you very much, Doctor.

507
00:38:20,040 --> 00:38:22,080
Why didn't I know he had heart disease?

508
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:39,640
Get some rest.

509
00:38:39,720 --> 00:38:40,600
Grandpa.

510
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:45,680
You're okay, right?

511
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:49,320
What's that face?

512
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:51,520
I'm not dead yet.

513
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:55,200
Why didn't you tell me
you had heart disease?

514
00:38:56,360 --> 00:38:58,320
You shouldn't ask him right now.

515
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:01,280
You too.

516
00:39:02,160 --> 00:39:03,040
Why didn't you tell me?

517
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:07,160
I asked him not to tell you.

518
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:10,160
Why, Grandpa?

519
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:12,200
I'm your granddaughter.

520
00:39:12,280 --> 00:39:15,120
If you're sick, I should be informed.

521
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:16,280
It's just heart disease.

522
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:18,440
It's nothing serious.

523
00:39:19,120 --> 00:39:22,520
If nothing had upset him,
this wouldn't have happened.

524
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:27,800
That's true.

525
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:29,200
In that case,

526
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:31,600
you should find out

527
00:39:31,680 --> 00:39:34,240
who leaked
that video and caused all of this.

528
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:37,400
I want to know too

529
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:41,520
if the person who did that
has a mother to teach them?

530
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:45,760
Or if they get it from their mother.

531
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:57,760
I'm going to step outside for some air.

532
00:40:06,880 --> 00:40:08,320
Grandpa.

533
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:11,400
I'm fine now.

534
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:14,280
Go home.

535
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:17,640
Chan, please take her home.

536
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:25,320
Aren't you going to ask me about
the livestream of me fighting with Cha?

537
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:28,320
I know what kind of person you are.

538
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:31,920
Go home.

539
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,200
I want to sleep.

540
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:00,040
Auntie.

541
00:41:06,680 --> 00:41:08,160
Who are you waiting for?

542
00:41:10,120 --> 00:41:11,640
I'm waiting for my niece.

543
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:16,360
Then I'll keep you company.

544
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:19,200
No need. You can go.

545
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:22,320
- I don't want to bother you.
- It's no bother, Auntie. I'm free.

546
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:23,640
I'll keep you company.

547
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:33,040
You must love your niece very much.

548
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:35,800
I see you waiting for her every day.

549
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:39,720
Of course I do.

550
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:41,200
I love her so much.

551
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:46,720
But you know what?

552
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:48,680
I think you should hurry home.

553
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:51,160
I just walked past your house,

554
00:41:51,240 --> 00:41:53,600
and I think I saw your niece there.

555
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:56,200
- You saw my niece?
- Yes.

556
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:57,360
Oh, come on.

557
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:58,920
I'll walk with you.

558
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:00,960
- Let's go.
- Come on.

559
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:05,200
- Auntie, slow down. Watch your step.
- Let's go.

560
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:06,880
- Come on.
- Be careful.

561
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:10,280
I'll leave you here then.

562
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:12,480
Thank you.

563
00:42:12,560 --> 00:42:13,840
Get home safely.

564
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:15,080
Okay.

565
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:33,200
<i>"Read."</i>

566
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:37,160
ME AND MY AUNT,
LOY KRATHONG DAY, GRADE 2

567
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:46,720
MY GOOD GIRL

568
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:03,240
DO YOU REMEMBER ME YET?

569
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:10,160
"My name is Jinla.

570
00:43:10,880 --> 00:43:12,560
I'm your niece, Lin."

571
00:43:20,840 --> 00:43:23,440
Oh, my bags are so heavy.

572
00:43:27,280 --> 00:43:29,000
Was that fun for you?

573
00:43:29,080 --> 00:43:30,880
Why didn't you tell me you were her?

574
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:36,440
If I told you, would you remember me?

575
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:39,560
Do you know
you once shouted for the police

576
00:43:39,640 --> 00:43:41,360
because you thought I was gonna hurt you?

577
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:44,520
And then what? Did they arrest you?

578
00:43:44,600 --> 00:43:46,560
No, Aunt.

579
00:43:46,640 --> 00:43:48,320
Because I'm good-looking.

580
00:43:48,400 --> 00:43:50,400
So they didn't believe I was a criminal.

581
00:43:52,560 --> 00:43:54,640
Since I can't remember anything,

582
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:56,080
you can say whatever you want.

583
00:43:57,720 --> 00:43:58,840
Have you eaten yet?

584
00:43:58,920 --> 00:44:00,240
Yes, I have.

585
00:44:01,400 --> 00:44:02,720
That's right.

586
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:05,440
I submitted the draft.

587
00:44:05,520 --> 00:44:07,440
I have a small favor to ask.

588
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:11,320
Could you transfer part of the payment
in advance? Maybe half?

589
00:44:11,840 --> 00:44:15,600
Oh, that's okay. Sure, you got it.
I can wait for the full payment.

590
00:44:16,520 --> 00:44:17,480
Yes.

591
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:33,360
Jin.

592
00:44:34,280 --> 00:44:35,760
I'm sorry.

593
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:38,360
Actually,

594
00:44:39,120 --> 00:44:41,920
you should be going out with your friends

595
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:47,000
or living your own life
like everyone else.

596
00:44:47,080 --> 00:44:53,120
Instead, you have to take care
of your old and sick aunt.

597
00:44:53,200 --> 00:44:54,640
I'm sorry.

598
00:44:56,440 --> 00:45:00,680
Geez, who said I wanted to live
like everyone else?

599
00:45:00,760 --> 00:45:03,120
Nothing beats living with you.

600
00:45:10,960 --> 00:45:16,080
AVAILABLE BALANCE: 15,000.00

601
00:45:20,200 --> 00:45:21,720
Hey.

602
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:23,760
If you want to repay me,

603
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:25,600
I have a job for you.

604
00:45:28,080 --> 00:45:29,040
What job?

605
00:45:32,520 --> 00:45:34,840
<i>I'll take the job you mentioned.</i>

606
00:45:34,920 --> 00:45:37,040
<i>Who am I interviewing tomorrow?</i>

607
00:45:37,120 --> 00:45:41,040
I'LL TAKE THE JOB YOU MENTIONED.
WHO AM I INTERVIEWING TOMORROW?

608
00:45:42,720 --> 00:45:44,320
<i>Okay, bestie.</i>

609
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:48,040
<i>This is the person</i>
<i>you're interviewing tomorrow.</i>

610
00:45:48,120 --> 00:45:52,320
OKAY, BESTIE. THIS IS THE PERSON
YOU'RE INTERVIEWING TOMORROW.

611
00:45:52,400 --> 00:45:53,840
Socialite Claire.

612
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:57,360
Khaedarun Kanchathara.

613
00:45:59,000 --> 00:46:01,040
<i>Before you meet Ms. Claire,</i>

614
00:46:01,120 --> 00:46:03,880
<i>I'd like to explain the process</i>
<i>and details again.</i>

615
00:46:04,560 --> 00:46:06,240
After the interview,

616
00:46:06,320 --> 00:46:08,320
you must send me the draft to review.

617
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:10,840
And no matter which media outlet
you publish it through,

618
00:46:10,920 --> 00:46:12,600
I have to review it again.

619
00:46:13,200 --> 00:46:14,080
Got it.

620
00:46:14,160 --> 00:46:18,000
You may think we're
being strict and protecting Ms. Claire,

621
00:46:18,080 --> 00:46:21,200
but actually, we're protecting you.

622
00:46:22,440 --> 00:46:23,800
Protecting me?

623
00:46:24,520 --> 00:46:26,160
Ms. Claire is a public figure

624
00:46:26,240 --> 00:46:28,440
and a senior executive at TGL.

625
00:46:28,520 --> 00:46:30,760
If anything damaging gets out,

626
00:46:30,840 --> 00:46:32,840
I'm afraid our legal department

627
00:46:32,920 --> 00:46:35,800
may have to sue you and your company.

628
00:46:37,920 --> 00:46:40,200
That sounds like a threat.

629
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:42,560
Don't think of it that way.

630
00:46:42,640 --> 00:46:45,080
I'd like you to think we truly mean well.

631
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:47,560
And she's recently been in the news,

632
00:46:47,640 --> 00:46:49,840
Mr. Chan needs to be strict about this.

633
00:46:51,200 --> 00:46:53,360
- Mr. Chan?
- Yes.

634
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:55,440
- Mr. Chan--
- Please.

635
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:57,080
Ms. Claire is waiting inside.

636
00:46:59,160 --> 00:47:00,040
Okay.

637
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:09,640
- Please.
- Okay.

638
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:22,240
<i>What happened to him?</i>

639
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:24,800
Why did he need a thrombolytic?

640
00:47:24,880 --> 00:47:27,520
Mr. Thiwa had
an acute myocardial infarction.

641
00:47:46,120 --> 00:47:47,040
Hello.

642
00:47:53,080 --> 00:47:54,440
Ms. Claire?

643
00:47:57,400 --> 00:47:58,800
Ms. Claire!

644
00:48:18,320 --> 00:48:19,480
Who are you?

645
00:48:19,560 --> 00:48:21,280
I'm Jinla.

646
00:48:21,360 --> 00:48:22,320
From <i>The Contenic.</i>

647
00:48:22,920 --> 00:48:24,440
<i>Are you really not coming with us?</i>

648
00:48:24,520 --> 00:48:27,480
I hope you didn't tell the pilot
to crash the helicopter.

649
00:48:33,520 --> 00:48:35,560
Claire's helicopter really crashed?
